page.title: 08HOUSING: CHERRY WILLINGHAM
page.content: In Cherry Willingham most people live on estates. These homes are usually either bungalows or detatched houses. Houses in any street are usually different in style although overall there are not many different types in the village. Most houses and bungalows are of two/three bedrooms. Most of the houses have been built since the 1950's. In Reepham there are no real estates just a collection of houses and bungalows arranged in streets. Many of the houses were built before the last war and are quite large. Both Cherry Willingham and Reepham have Manor houses but neither is particularly important today. Development is taking place in both villages on a small scale although 300 new houses are planned for Cherry Willingham. M.CHAMBERS
